comments: Dinwiddie (BKN) and Burks (PHI) make incidental contact after Dinwiddie releases the ball at the end of the drive.
Embiid (PHI) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie (BKN) that does not affect his ability to pass at the end of the drive.
Dinwiddie (BKN) extends his hand into Richardson's (PHI) front in transition and affects his SQBR.
Embiid (PHI) slightly extends his elbow as he sets the pick in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path, but the contact is marginal.
Dinwiddie (BKN) is not in a legal guarding position when he initiates contact with Burks (PHI) that affects his SQBR.
Richardson (PHI) and Dinwiddie (BKN) briefly engage and separate off-ball.
Jordan (BKN) receives the pass and lands in a jump stop, but he moves both feet without dribbling before releasing the ball.
Dinwiddie (BKN) extends his leg as part of a natural shooting motion on the jump shot attempt and the contact with Embiid (PHI) is marginal.
Richardson (PHI) reaches back and clamps Jordan's (BKN) leg and restricts his ability to reach for the rebound.
Richardson (PHI) briefly engages with Dinwiddie (BKN) but does not hold his hip or arm prior to deflecting the pass.
Dinwiddie (BKN) makes marginal contact with Richardson (PHI) as he disengages from the contact during the loose ball situation.
LeVert (BKN) extends his arm forward and grabs and turns Richardson's (PHI) side which restricts his ability to reach for the loose ball.
Embiid (PHI) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie (BKN) after releasing the pass in transition.
Thybulle (PHI) and LeVert (BKN) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Chandler (BKN) makes contact with Embiid's (PHI) arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Dinwiddie (BKN) takes fewer than three steps after he has gathered the ball.
Richardson (PHI) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (BKN) holds Embiid's (PHI) arm and affects his FOM off-ball.
Dinwiddie (BKN) moves his foot heel-to-toe to create space.
Embiid (PHI) absorbs the contact initiated by Chandler (BKN) and cleanly blocks the shot attempt.
